  "name": "RC Filter Demo",
  "lesson": {
    "title": "RC Filter Demo",
    "description": "Turn the pot slowly — the red LED follows brightness through a low-pass filter (1kΩ + 100µF to ground, τ ≈ 0.1 s). Wiggle the knob quickly and the LED barely changes: the RC network passes slow changes and blocks fast ones. Compare lesson 14 (no capacitor), where the LED tracks every twitch. Pot 270° on column 5; filter node on column 6; cap on column 5 with + toward the junction; LED east at 90°."
  },
